MBOMBELA &#8211; Police confirmed that the quad bike accident had happened on a dirt road near Blue Moon soon after 10:00.Capt Dawie Pretorius said the quad bike had gone off the road and had landed on the 16-year-old, who was the passenger. He added there was a police inquest into culpable homicide.Also read: Youth Day: Advice for and from millennialsNetcare 911 reports from the accident scene indicated that the bike with two occupants was travelling down a hill when it veered off the road and overturned. Exact details are still speculative and will form part of the police investigation, the company said. Photo: Netcare 911 Facebook pageAccording to a statement on the Netcare 911 Facebook page, &#8220;(The) advanced Life Support paramedics and team arrived at the scene and found that (the) 16-year-old-girl (who) was a passenger on the bike, hit a large rock as she was flung from the four wheeler.&#8221;Also read: EXPOSED: Three alleged brothels in Mbombela &#8220;Paramedics worked fervently at the scene for some time to try to resuscitate the girl, tragically, despite all their efforts she was declared dead at the scene,&#8221; it read.Netcare 911 paramedics and management also extended their heartfelt condolences to the family and friends of the young girl during this difficult time.